f="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showMessage?topicID=179.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showMessage?topicID=180.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=95%><tr><td bgcolor=#FFFFFF><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#333366 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#333366 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ugregar1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gregar1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#778899>(11/29/01 8:38:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Buff Beggers: A new twist</span><hr size=1> I am so torn by this issue nowadays.  Sometimes I remember that our charter spells out explicitly that we are obligated to help others.  Sometimes I think all the well-meaning elders, myself included, created the  - first beg, then demand, then expect that &quot;MY EPIC, etc. is a gods-given right&quot;, mentality that seems to run rampant in Norrath nowadays.  I really don't know.  Chicken or the egg first?  All I know is that not having a lot of folks ANYWHERE who could SOW or bind for the first 20 levels of Norrathian life, seems to make me appreciate ANY mana-costing kindness more.<br>
<br>
The FIRST person I SOW, heal, buff, etc. is the low person who comes to the zone where I am standing, torn and bleeding from a close fight, sits down, and doesn't ask a soul for anything.  The SECOND is the person who asks politely and doesn't demand.  An offer of a donation is fine, but I've never accepted pp for spending mana to help someone.  I am a Ridgerunner.  <br>
<br>
A call for help across many zones?  Well, there again, how is the request phrased?  What is my current situation, especially if I am in a group?  If I'm in a group of RR's, nine times out of ten, we all go. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  If it's not a CR situation for the asker, then yes, I feel it's only fair they travel to me to receive what they've asked for.  Lizz, my constant partner, faces different circumstances.  She can rezz.  There again, our charter specifically says if helping isn't futile or won't cause you, or your group, to die needlessly, it's a duty.<br>
<br>
Lizz is a halfling cleric, I am a half-elf ranger.  Our biggest laughs come when both she and I are asked for ports.  Halfling = druid, apparently in spite of purple plate armor.  I get asked for ports because /who says I am a pathfinder.  Our favorite chuckle is when someone runs up to both of us and asks, &quot;Lizz, may I please get a SOW?&quot; I immediately SOW them, and they thank Lizz, sometimes offering her a donation. <br>
I think a Thank You is great, even if misplaced. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
My worst nightmare was a rezz request in DL.  The person was back in G Fay.  He asked Lizz for a rezz.<br>
Nope, he had no idea where his corpse was.  Lizz was running to join me at KC from FV.  So, I camoed, SOWed, and began searching for the body.  I actually divided the DL zone into search quadrants in my mind, and proceeded to search.  Approximately 40 minutes later, I found the body, got consent, and dragged the corpse to Lizz outside Karnors.  Then, the dreaded &quot;What level cleric are you?&quot; came to Lizz.  Followed by the &quot;nm, I'll wait for a higher level rezz&quot;.  If I were not a Ridgerunner, that body would've been dragged immediately back to it's original resting place.  Loot,including &quot;epics&quot;, is meaningless to me, pp's are meaningless to me, levels are meaningless to me.  The precious treasure in Norrath, for me, is the quality of my time spent there.<br>
<br>
As long as Gregar has existed in Norrath, I've made a point of visiting any nearby newbie zone, and spending time there buffing, SOWing, healing, and answering questions.  And, yes, it's nice that a 52nd ranger heal DOES mean more than diddle-squat there. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I've done that for two purposes.  One, to pass on the kindness of beta players, way back when, who did the same for me.  And two, to keep an eye out for the real newbies who are going to be future RR's.  Over the course of time, Demands have increased, Thank You has decreased dramatically.  Guess which ones I remember for the future?<br>
<br>
Gregar Mataennoo<br>
Ridgerunner<br>
Ranger 52nd  <br>
