ok, actually on the topic of this thread now ) I am fairly non-twinked, and still have a CCS on my cleric. I get asked for clarity more than anything else. Must be the light blue. I usually hit them with Invis vs. Undead (in a zone with no undeads) or a lvl 1 buff and then ask them for a buff they don't have.<br>
<br>
The absolute best just happened the other day in Befallen (getting a corpse stick). Was sitting there, waiting for the respawn of the SK when I get a tell asking me if I can revive him in Befallen. I do /who. It's a lvl 10 warrior who was in EC. Gotta love alts. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/umarttog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marttog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#778899>(11/30/01 10:17:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Buff Beggers: A new twist</span><hr size=1> I had at least 2 fun times with buff beggers.<br>
<br>
The day I got my Velious caster's leather tunic I was in GD with a group of guildies.   They had just commented that I looked like a druid, when someone ran up to the group:<br>
<br>
begger:  Hail Marrtog<br>
begger:  can u sow me plz?<br>
Me:       No, I can't<br>
begger:  plz, plz <br>
Me:       I'd really love to, but I can't<br>
begger:  Plz, I have a long way to run.  plz sow me<br>
<br>
By this time, the entire group was ROFL.   I explained that I'm a wizard and everyone in the group buffed him.<br>
<br>
